licensed only five bot power projects however increasing domestic electricity demand has attracted foreign investors to the country’s power sector although vietnam’s economy is still in a downturn the electricity demand in the first half of this year rose    per cent year on year the  moit estimated that the demand would continue to increase from  to  per cent next year by phuong thu latest news mediplast inaugurates new factory in bac ninh    pm values samsung’s investment in vn    dragon capital to invest in  million solar farm in can tho    viettel makes bank from international markets    the ultraclear float glass facility to start construction    asean creates a base in vietnam    global infra investment need to reach  trillion by      billion vung ro refinery and petrochemical project warned over long delay    investors warned about oversupply of condotels    pm okays van don ez development    latest news vietnammade luxury handbags enter us market    transfer pricing still leaving ugly legacy    vn leading fertilizer producer to expand agribusiness in cambodia    race to embrace retail mall revolution    air mekong looking to avoid turbulence    tnkbp grabs troubled bp’s assets    evn telecom steps up    gold treads water    more news pm calls on chinese investors to heed technology environment    thai binh economic zone to be established    nghi son  thermal power plant to be kicked off by yearend    siemens’ gateway to a digital future    the wary balance of the marketbased economy    vietnamese textile sector overcomes tpp fallback in style    hard rock interested in developing casino at laguna lang co    taiwan eyes vietnamese healthcare sector    new wave of billiondollar fdi projects hits vietnam    gov’t pledges to create favorable conditions for malaysian investors    more most viewedmost recommended  billion long son petrochemical complex to resume construction the construction of the  billion long son petrochemical complex in the southern province o